  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now it came to pass on a certain day,.... The same day at even, as Mark says, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 4:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in which he delivered the parables of the sower, and of the seed cast into the ground, and of the grain of mustard seed: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that he went into a ship with his disciples; they following him into it, Matthew 8:23",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that he went into a ship with his disciples; they following him into it, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 8:23",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he said unto them, let us go over unto the other side of the lake; of Gennesaret, or sea of Galilee: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they launched forth; into the sea; they set sail, and proceeded: this clause is omitted in the Syriac and Persic versions. ",
        "children": [
